Summary
MongoDB VM (mongo):

MongoDB is installed and running.
OpenVPN server is configured and running.
Backup VM (backup):

mongodump is installed.
A backup directory is created.
A cron job is set up to perform daily backups of the MongoDB database.
The project is now fully set up with MongoDB running on one VM, backups being taken regularly on another VM, and secure communication between the VMs through a VPN. This setup ensures data redundancy and security for your MongoDB instance.






